modules.description: Provides functions to convert OCaml data structures into JavaScript-compatible formats, including lists, records, and variants. Works with primitive types, arrays, and custom type representations. Enables seamless integration of OCaml code in JavaScript environments by serializing values for use in web applications.

Exports a value as the default export in a CommonJS module, binding it to the module's exports object. Works with arbitrary OCaml values and integrates with JavaScript environments that support CommonJS syntax. Used to expose functions or data structures to JavaScript code requiring module exports.
